Celtic 2 St Mirren 0 Second-half goals from Cameron Carter-Vickers and Callum McGregor earned Celtic another crucial three Scottish Premiership points against St Mirren at Parkhead. Carter-Vickers lashed home from close range to ease the tension 10 minutes after the break after Celtic had struggled to cut through a well-drilled visiting team. The opener did not open the floodgates by any means but Celticâ€™s lead was never threatened before McGregor doubled it in the 81st minute when he drilled home from inside the box. The 2-0 victory kept the leaders three points clear of Rangers with nine games remaining, with the defending champions winning 1-0 win away to St Johnstone thanks to a third-minute goal from Glen Kamara.